Chardikla Time TV North America is your go-to destination for authentic Punjabi content. Watch live now and stay connected to your roots!

It features news analysis, talk shows, crime series, documentaries, and social discussions. Catering to all age groups, it offers diverse content and strong engagement, making it a trusted choice for advertisers and viewers worldwide.

Chardikla Gurbaani TV, with the motto “A Bliss to Humanity,” is a 24×7 Free Sikh Devotional Channel available globally on various platforms. It features live telecasts from Takhat Sri Harimandir Ji Patna Sahib, Gurdwara Sri Bangla Sahib, and special broadcasts from North America. Dedicated to Sikh teachings, history, Katha, Kirtan, and Dhadhi shows, it spreads the message of Gurbani worldwide.

programme.title: Aussie bowlers take the honours on opening day | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | First Test, Day 1
programme.desc: Mitchell Starc set the tone with a wicket off the game's second ball, Nathan Lyon created plenty of chances before removing Cheteshwar Pujara, and Virat Kohli was run out to spark a mini-collapse against the new pink ball on an entertaining first day

programme.title: India take upper hand in enthralling day-night Test | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | First Test, Day 2
programme.desc: A wicket just before stumps gave Australia a late boost after India took a handy first-innings lead on day two of the first Vodafone Test in Adelaide

programme.title: Adelaide amazes again | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | First Test, Day 3
programme.desc: Australia started day three looking to limit India's first innings lead, they ended it with an eight-wicket win in under two sessions of play after one of the more remarkable days of Test cricket

programme.title: India’s bowlers fire on entertaining Boxing Day | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Second Test, Day 1
programme.desc: Eleven wickets fell on the opening day of the second Vodafone Test as India responded to their defeat in Adelaide by rattling Australia’s batters

programme.title: Rahane's unbeaten ton puts India on top | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Second Test, Day 2
programme.desc: Stand-in India captain Ajinkya Rahane has filled Virat Kohli's imposing shoes in impeccable style with his 12th Test century lifting the tourists to an 82-run first-innings lead over Australia in the second Test

programme.title: Superb India take control after Aussie batting disaster | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Second Test, Day 3
programme.desc: After being bowled out for 326, India ran through Australia's batting order to the tune of 6-133 on an eventful day three of the second Vodafone Test

programme.title: India level series at MCG with convincing eight-wicket win | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Second Test, Day 4
programme.desc: Australia rookie Cameron Green put up a fight with a well-made 45 but the home side could only manage a 69-run lead, which India rattled off with minimal fuss despite the early loss of two wickets

programme.title: Labuschagne, Pucovski fifties boost Aussies amid the rain | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Third Test, Day 1
programme.desc: Test debutant Will Pucovski hit an assured and composed 62 in his maiden knock while Marnus Labuschagne finished unbeaten on 67 as the pair dominated the first day where only 55 overs were possible amid traditional Sydney rain

programme.title: Late wickets boost Australia after Smith hundred | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Third Test, Day 2
programme.desc: India's bowlers fought back impressively on day two of the third Test before two late wickets brought Australia back into the match

programme.title: Bowling, fielding gives Australia edge | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Third Test, Day 3
programme.desc: Three run outs and another excellent Australian bowling performance has handed Australia the upper hand over India after three days of the third Test

programme.title: Aussies grab late wickets after Green, Smith fire | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Third Test, Day 4
programme.desc: Cameron Green posted his highest Test score and Steve Smith impressed again before Australia removed both openers as India look to stave off defeat in the third Test

programme.title: Brave India pull off the great escape at the SCG | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Third Test, Day 5
programme.desc: A hobbled Hanuma Vihari and a battered Ravichandran Ashwin defy Australia's bowlers for the entire final session after Rishabh Pant and Cheteshwar Pujara laid the platform for a famous drawn Test

programme.title: Honours split on day one at the Gabba | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Fourth Test, Day 1
programme.desc: Marnus Labuschagne's century was the highlight for the hosts, while India's rookie bowling attack took up the fight to Australia on day one of the fourth Test in Brisbane

programme.title: Cummins and Lyon strike for Aussies before storm arrives | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Fourth Test, Day 2
programme.desc: India reached 2-62 at the Gabba before the rain arrived, frustrating Australia's hunt for wickets on day two

programme.title: India lower order frustrates Aussies with Test evenly poised | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Fourth Test, Day 3
programme.desc: A 123-run partnership between Washington Sundar and Shardul Thakur saw India bowled out just 33 runs short of Australia's first innings, with Josh Hazlewood claiming a five-wicket haul, before Australia's openers extended their lead to 54 by stumps

programme.title: Siraj five, Smith runs help set stage for grand finale | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Fourth Test, Day 4
programme.desc: Australia entered day four looking to press on to build a big lead, but five wickets to Mohammed Siraj and four for Shardul Thakur pegged the home side back, with Steve Smith the only player passing 50, setting up an epic day five finish.

programme.title: India claim stunning series win | RAPID REWIND | 2020/21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy | Fourth Test, Day 5
programme.desc: Rishabh Pant was the hero as an injury-ravaged India ended Australia's 32-year undefeated run at the Gabba, executing a record-breaking final day chase to win the Test by three wickets and the series 2-1
